## Code Style

### React/TypeScript
```typescript
// Use functional components with hooks
const Component = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState<Type>(initialValue);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    // Side effects
    return () => {
      // Cleanup
    };
  }, [dependencies]);
  
  return <div>...</div>;
};

// Type all props
interface Props {
  name: string;
  optional?: boolean;
}

// Use descriptive variable names
const isEnvelopeOpen = true; // ✅
const x = true; // ❌
```

### Tailwind CSS
```typescript
// Use only core utility classes (no custom classes beyond config)
// Organize classes logically: layout → spacing → colors → typography
<div className="flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-8 bg-cream text-burgundy font-playfair text-4xl">

// Use custom colors from palette
<div className="bg-[#F5EFE7] text-[#8B4B5C]">
```

### Framer Motion
```typescript
// Always specify transitions
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.8, ease: [0.43, 0.13, 0.23, 0.96] }}
>

// Use variants for complex sequences
const variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, transition: { duration: 0.5 } }
};
```

## What to Avoid

### Design Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Generic wedding templates
- ❌ Overly playful or casual design
- ❌ Beach party aesthetics (this is elegant tropical)
- ❌ Cluttered layouts
- ❌ Too many animations (keep it sophisticated)
- ❌ Bullet points in prose content
- ❌ Tiny text or poor contrast

### Code Anti-Patterns
- ❌ localStorage/sessionStorage usage
- ❌ Slow or janky animations
- ❌ Missing loading states
- ❌ No error handling
- ❌ Hardcoded values that should be constants
- ❌ Missing TypeScript types
- ❌ Broken mobile layouts
- ❌ Allowing scroll during envelope animation

## Testing Checklist

